  <eainfo>
    <overview>
      <eaover>Binary data file: Trace data are available as binary files in SEG-Y format. These files have a .SEG extension and range in size from 41 to 284 MB.</eaover>
      <eaover>Graphic image file: Printable profiles are available as GIF images. Interactive profiles are available as HTML pages with accompanying JPEG images. The line navigation maps and trackline maps are JPEG images. The trackline maps contain links to the seismic profiles and line navigation maps.</eaover>
      <eaover>Navigation file: Navigation files are available as ASCII text files. Provided are raw (unprocessed) shotpoint navigation files, processed shotpoint navigation files, and processed 1,000-shot-interval location files.</eaover>
      <eaover>GIS file: The GIS project used to create the trackline maps is provided as a zip file composed of ESRI map documents, shapefiles, and metadata.</eaover>
      <eadetcit>Barry, K.M., Cavers, D.A., and Kneale, C.W., 1975, Recommended standards for digital tape formats: Geophysics, v. 40, no. 2, p. 344-352. Also available online at: http://www.seg.org/publications/tech-stand.</eadetcit>
      <eadetcit>Zihlman, F.N., 1992, DUMPSEGY V1.0: A program to examine the contents of SEG-Y disk-image seismic data: U.S. Geological Survey Open-File Report 92-590, 28 p. Also available online at http://pubs.er.usgs.gov/usgspubs/ofr/ofr92590.</eadetcit>
    </overview>
  </eainfo>
